Workflow for Setting Up Google Analytics and Google Tag Manager

To configure Vlocity OmniAnalytics to send data to Google Analytics with Enhanced Ecommerce, prepare Google Analytics and Google Tag Manager as follows:

Create an Account and Property in Google Analytics.
Create a View in Google Analytics.
Create an Account in Google Tag Manager.
Create a Google Analytics Tracking ID Variable in Google Tag Manager.
Create Data Layer Variables in Google Tag Manager.
Create Triggers in Google Tag Manager.
Create the Page View Tag in Google Tag Manager.
Create the Event Tag in Google Tag Manager.

Whatâ€™s next: Workflow for Adding Ecommerce Data to the Example OmniScript and Card.

The first step when you set up Google Analytics is to create an account and a property. The property contains metadata for the account.

Creating a view lets you enable Ecommerce settings and define checkout steps for the example OmniScript.

Though related to Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager is a separate application that requires a separate account.

Creating this variable lets you specify the Tracking ID once and then reference it in multiple places.

Creating data layer variables lets you create fewer and more versatile event tags.

Triggers define when tags are invoked.

The Page View Tag is invoked every time a tracked page is loaded.

The Event Tag is invoked every time an event occurs in a tracked page.
title: Setting Up Google Analytics and Google Tag Manager with OmniAnalytics
